doc.previous: Tejas' Final Operational Clearance (FOC) was reportedly delayed from December 2012 until mid-2013 or later.[78][79] The Tejas programme has enlisted EADS to help expand the flight envelope to meet service requirements.[80]
doc.after: On 9 March 2012, LSP-7 took to its maiden flight from HAL airport.[22] The Naval LCA made its first flight, almost two years after being rolled out, on 27 April 2012.[81]
